Kim Yong Nam arrives in Tarabulus 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tarabulus, July 13 (KCNA correspondent) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, arrived in Tarabulus this morning by a special plane to pay an official goodwill visit to the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya at the invitation of Col. Moammer El Gaddafi, the leader of the Great September First Revolution of the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya.
 Also arriving with him were Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun, Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Kwang Gun, president of the Academy of Sciences Ri Kwang Ho, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were greeted at the airport by Major General Mustafa al Kharoubi, member of the historical leadership of the Great September First Revolution, Gais Lbrahim, general coordinator of the social people's leadership, Al Zinati Mohamed al Zinati, Secretary of the General People's Congress, and other leading officials of Libya and Choe In Sop, DPRK Ambassador to Libya, his embassy officials and foreign diplomatic envoys here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A function took place in welcome of Kim Yong Nam at the airport. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam in his arrival statement issued at the airport said he was pleased to see at first hand the successes made by the friendly Libyan people in their efforts to build a free, prosperous new society under the slogan of "Jamahiriya" under the guidance of Col. Moammer El Gaddafi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement expressed conviction that his visit which was taking place in the significant year marking the 20th anniversary of the DPRK-Libya Treaty of the Alliance on Friendship and Cooperation would offer an important occasion in consolidating the friendly ties between the two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day Kim Yong Nam had a friendly talk with Major General Mustafa al Kharoubi.

Rally for national reunification held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- The solidarity for implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly held a rally for national reunification in Chongwon, North Chungchong Province, on July 6 and 7.
 The participants vowed to dynamically turn out in the struggle to implement the June 15 Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution adopted at the rally called for focusing all efforts on the anti-U.S., anti-war and anti-nuke struggle, frustrating the plot of the pro-U.S. conservative forces to ditch the declaration and escalating the movement for implementing it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting nobody can block all the fellow countrymen's grand march for reunification under the uplifted slogan "Let's reunify the country by the concerted efforts of our nation," the resolution called on all the people to make this a fruitful year in the efforts for the country's reunification.

Bush's apology demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- The headquarters of the All-People Movement for the Withdrawal of the U.S. Troops reportedly demanded an apology of Bush, who is chiefly to blame for the two girl students killed by a U.S. armored car, and the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from South Korea.
 Setting out a slogan for its actions, the South Korean organization on July 11 called for driving the U.S. troops, a group of killers, out of South Korea, reunifying the country by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation and implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The slogan called for a coup de grace to the Joson Ilbo newspaper and Ri Hoe Chang's Grand National Party, which are patronizing the U.S. troops. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the art troupe of the South Korean Federation of University Student Councils created a song "May you return to life to become flowers" in commemoration of the two victims and posted it together with its musical note on its Internet homepage.

U.S. history woven with aggression and plunder 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article says that the U.S. nature of aggression and plunder still remains unchanged.
 The 50 stars on the U.S. flag provide a glimpse of its history of aggression and plunder, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the wars carried out by the U.S. imperialists against other countries are all those of aggression and plunder. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Finding it is no longer possible to dominate, rule and plunder other countries in a forcible way, they are now employing a more concealed and crafty way in exploitation and plunder of the countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Typical of it is exploitation and plunder through multinational companies. The U.S. transnational companies have invested in developing countries undergoing economic woes under the pretext of "aid" and squeezed a profit of four or five dollars, even 10 dollars per one dollar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is also escalating exploitation and plunder through "loan." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Besides, under the cloak of "joint development" and "technical cooperation" it is expanding its interests by taking a grasp of the major economic sectors of developing countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world progressives should clearly know the U.S. imperialists' nature and wage a staunch struggle against aggression and plunder to make the new century free from exploitation and plunder, domination and subjugation.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's work on national reunification marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- The fellow countrymen in the north, south and overseas should join in the efforts to implement the North-South Joint Declaration based on the three principles of national reunification.
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article devoted to the 30th anniversary of the publication of leader Kim Jong Il's work "Let Us Struggle Resolutely To Implement The Three Principles Of National Reunification". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work discloses the reactionary nature of the anti-reunification elements rejecting the implementation of the July 4 Joint Statement, explains the validity and significance of the three principles -- independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity -- and clarifies all issues regarding their implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article notes that the last 30 years clearly proved the validity, significance and vitality of the ideas and theories formulated in the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First of all, the work serves as precious, historic wealth because it implants consciousness of national independence in the fellow countrymen, it says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National independence is a banner of the struggle all the Koreans should uplift, as the reunification issue in Korea spawned by foreign forces and the U.S. imperialists have occupied a half of the country and stood in the way of its reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic inter-Korean summit meeting in Pyongyang and the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration are a brilliant result of Kim Jong Il's idea of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work is a banner that provided a practical foundation of national reunification to the fellow countrymen and inspires them to turn out in the efforts for the reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the fellow countrymen who love the country and the nation and wish for national reunification should firmly unite under the banner of the three principles of national reunification and the June 15 Joint Declaration and smash the U.S. imperialists and South Korean anti-reunification elements' moves of confrontation and war.

DPRK-Libya talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Tarabulus, July 13 (KCNA correspondent) -- Talks took place in Tarabulus on Saturday between the sides of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya.
 The sides discussed developing, as required by the new century, bilateral relations of friendship forged in the anti-imperialist struggle for independence on the basis of the intimacy between President Kim Il Sung and Col. Moammer El Gaddafi. They also exchanged views on some matters of common concern and reached a consensus on the discussed issues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK side said that the Korean people have convincingly stepped up the building of a powerful nation under Kim Jong Il's army-based leadership, overcoming manifold difficulties. It also explained the principled stand of the Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK government for an early independent reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK side expressed support and solidarity for the Libyan people in their just struggle to smash the imperialists' anti-Libya moves, defend the sovereignty and independence of the country and build a new country independent and prosperous.
 The Libyan side appreciated the fact that the Korean people have undauntedly defended their just cause with an indomitable will and registered tremendous achievements in socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It reaffirmed support for the Korean people's just efforts for reunifying the country with the efforts of the nation and expressed the belief that Korean reunification would be achieved as early as possible in an independent and peaceful way and without foreign interference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A friendly atmosphere prevailed in the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on the DPRK side were Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun, Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Kwang Gun, president of the Academy of Sciences Ri Kwang Ho, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol, DPRK Ambassador to Libya Choe In Sop, and suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sitting on its opposite side were Abdulrahman Mohamed Shalgham, Secretary of the General People's Committee for Foreign Relation and International Co-operation, Al-Ojaili Abdul-Salam Barini, Secretary of Finance, Ahmed Amer al Muakkaf, Secretary of the People's Bureau of the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya to the DPRK, and other officials concerned.
